      <title>Install sqlite3 on ubuntu by compiling from source code</title>
      <link href="/2020/03/13/Install-sqlite3-on-ubuntu-by-compiling-from-source-code/"/>
      <url>/2020/03/13/Install-sqlite3-on-ubuntu-by-compiling-from-source-code/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ol><li>prepare build tools if tools not ready<a id="more"></a><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">sudo apt-get install build-essential</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li>download source code package from <a href="https://www.sqlite.org/download.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.sqlite.org/download.html</a><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">curl -O https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.sqlite.org&#x2F;snapshot&#x2F;sqlite-snapshot-202003121754.tar.gz</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li>unzip and enter the dir<figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">tar xvzf sqlite...tar.gz</span><br><span class="line">cd sqlite...</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li>compile, build and install<figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">.&#x2F;configure</span><br><span class="line">make</span><br><span class="line">#if failed, try &quot;make clean&quot; and run &quot;make&quot; again</span><br><span class="line">sudo make install</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ol><p>Reference from:</p><ol><li><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19816275/no-acceptable-c-compiler-found-in-path-when-installing-python" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19816275/no-acceptable-c-compiler-found-in-path-when-installing-python</a></li><li>INSTALL doc in the package</li><li><blockquote><p>SQLite 安装</p><footer><strong>runoob.com</strong><cite><a href="https://www.runoob.com/sqlite/sqlite-installation.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.runoob.com/sqlite/sqlite-installation.html</a></cite></footer></blockquote></li></ol>]]></content>
      
      
